                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sheṭar</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">שטר</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>One of two copies of a Hebrew deed of sale of a house in Norwich in the parish of St. Peter, in Mancroft Street by Oshaya ben Isaac of York known as Ursel le Eveske of Norwich ben Deulecresse to William son of Roger of South Walsham.
								</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The deed of sale is preceded by a deed of remittance of the rights to the house by Miriam, Ursel's wife. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The deed is attested by Ursel ben Isaac, whose signature is witnessed by Isaac ben Samuel, Jacob ben Jacob, and Elijah ben Elijah. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Chirograph; for the other copy, see Lansdowne Ch 669. There are textual difference between the two copies, see Olszowy-Schlanger 2015, v.2, p.574-576.</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
